# SVARGA DIMSUM – AI MIGRATION AGENT RULES

# DOMAIN: https://svargadimsum.vercel.app/

## 🎯 OBJECTIVE

Migrate existing HTML, CSS, JS website into Next.js (App Router) with:

* ZERO design change
* ZERO feature loss
* Improved SEO (Google-compliant)
* Optimized performance using SSR, SSG, CSR appropriately

---

## 🚫 HARD RESTRICTIONS (ABSOLUTE – NO EXCEPTION)

1. DO NOT change:

   * UI design (layout, spacing, color, typography)
   * Component structure (visual hierarchy must remain identical)
   * Existing features or functionality
   * Content wording unless explicitly required for SEO

2. DO NOT:

   * Add new UI components
   * Remove existing sections
   * Replace design system (unless explicitly instructed)

3. ALL migrations must be:

   * Pixel-accurate
   * Functionally identical

---

## 🧱 MIGRATION STRUCTURE

### Convert HTML → Next.js Components

RULES:

* Each section becomes reusable component
* No inline HTML dumping
* Maintain semantic HTML (header, section, footer)

Example structure:

```
/app
  /page.js
/components
  Header.jsx
  Hero.jsx
  Menu.jsx
  Footer.jsx
```

---

## ⚙️ RENDERING STRATEGY (MANDATORY)

### SSG (Static Site Generation)

USE FOR:

* Landing page
* Menu page
* Outlet page
* Static content

GOAL:

* Fast load
* SEO friendly

---

### SSR (Server Side Rendering)

USE FOR:

* Dynamic content (if any future feature added)
* Real-time data

---

### CSR (Client Side Rendering)

USE ONLY WHEN:

* Interactive UI required
* Cart / state / animations

⚠️ DO NOT convert everything into CSR

---

## 🧭 ROUTING RULES

USE clean URLs:

GOOD:

* /menu/dimsum-mentai
* /outlet/cilodong

BAD:

* /menu?id=1
* /page?slug=abc

---

## 🔍 SEO STANDARDS (STRICT – GOOGLE COMPLIANT)

### Every page MUST have:

* Unique title
* Unique meta description
* Proper heading structure (H1 only one per page)

Example:

```js
export const metadata = {
  title: "Dimsum Mentai | Svarga Dimsum",
  description: "Dimsum mentai creamy dan gurih di Svarga Dimsum.",
};
```

---

### Dynamic SEO (REQUIRED for scalability)

Use:

```js
export async function generateMetadata({ params }) {
```

---

### IMAGE SEO

* Use Next.js `<Image />`
* MUST include `alt`
* File size optimized

---

## 🗺️ SITEMAP RULES (CRITICAL – FIX CURRENT ERROR)

### MUST generate valid sitemap.xml

Location:

```
/app/sitemap.js
```

Example:

```js
export default function sitemap() {
  return [
    {
      url: 'https://svargadimsum.vercel.app/',
      lastModified: new Date(),
    },
    {
      url: 'https://svargadimsum.vercel.app/menu',
      lastModified: new Date(),
    },
    {
      url: 'https://svargadimsum.vercel.app/outlet',
      lastModified: new Date(),
    },
  ];
}
```

---

### RULES:

* MUST return valid array
* MUST include full absolute URL
* MUST NOT return empty
* MUST NOT return invalid routes

---

## 🤖 ROBOTS.TXT (MANDATORY)

Create:

```
/public/robots.txt
```

Content:

```
User-agent: *
Allow: /

Sitemap: https://svargadimsum.vercel.app/sitemap.xml
```

---

## 🔐 SECURITY STANDARDS

* Sanitize all inputs
* Avoid exposing API keys
* Use environment variables (.env)
* Prevent XSS (no dangerouslySetInnerHTML unless necessary)
* Use HTTPS only (already handled by Vercel)

---

## ⚡ PERFORMANCE RULES

* Use Next.js Image Optimization
* Avoid unnecessary client components
* Lazy load non-critical components
* Minimize JS bundle size

---

## 🧪 VALIDATION CHECKLIST

Before deployment:

* [ ] All pages render correctly
* [ ] No layout shift
* [ ] SEO metadata exists per page
* [ ] Sitemap accessible at /sitemap.xml
* [ ] Robots.txt accessible
* [ ] No console error
* [ ] Lighthouse score ≥ 90

---

## 🚨 FAILURE CONDITIONS

Migration is INVALID if:

* Design differs from original
* Any feature is broken
* Sitemap error appears in Google Search Console
* Metadata duplicated
* Page not indexed

---

## 🧠 FINAL PRINCIPLE

“Preserve everything. Improve silently.”

DO NOT innovate.
DO NOT redesign.
ONLY optimize structure, SEO, and performance.
